Sec. 93.052. CERTIFICATE OF WEIGHT. (a) A public weigher
shall issue a certificate of weight to a buyer or shipper of citrus
fruit that is required to be weighed under this subchapter.
(b) The buyer shall deliver the certificate provided under this
section to the seller prior to making an accounting or settlement on
the transaction.
Acts 1981, 67th Leg., p. 1240, ch. 388, Sec. 1, eff. Sept. 1, 1981.

